				<p><p>EtherCAT as you have noticed is a actually a good option for real-time data transfer, but if by "normal operating system" you mean Windows, that's a bad choice.</p>

<p>You can get a Linux implementation of EtherCAT master from IgH (<a href="http://www.etherlab.org/en/ethercat/index.php" rel="nofollow">http://www.etherlab.org/en/ethercat/index.php</a>) which needs a real-time operating system, such as Linux patched with RTAI, Xenomai or RT-preempt.</p>

<p>Once you are able to acquire your data periodically, you can use the many freely available software packages under most GNU/Linux distributions to process them.</p>
</p><br>
