				<p><p>Which type of real-time are you seeking for? Hard-, soft- or near- RT?</p>

<p>I'm asking because I believe it's likely that near-RT fits your application, depending of course on the speed of the conveyor and the system responsiveness you require.</p>

<p>Near-RT does not need large implementation effort: for instance, on Windows you can easily reach up to 100 Hz computation linking against <a href="http://wiki.icub.org/yarpdoc/index.html" rel="nofollow">yarp</a>, which is a C++ lightweight library already integrated with OpenCV for vision processing.</p>

<p>Note that 100 Hz should be suitable for dealing with the normal camera frame rate (i.e. 33 Hz)</p>
</p><br>
